You are helping me build the production-ready DIMO telemetry worker architecture for SynqDrive in Node.js + TypeScript using NestJS, BullMQ, Redis, Prisma, and PostgreSQL.

Context:
SynqDrive is a modular multi-tenant SaaS platform for Rental, Fleet, and Taxi operations.
DIMO is the first telematics provider.
This worker is ONLY responsible for telemetry polling / telemetry fetch orchestration / telemetry normalization / telemetry persistence.
It is NOT responsible for vehicle registration, product licensing, auth/RBAC, battery reference enrichment, brake reference enrichment, or tire manual data flows.

------------------------------------------------
CURRENT SYNQDRIVE RULES
------------------------------------------------

1. DIMO is already the trusted source for:
- VIN
- Make
- Model
- Year
- Fuel Type

These identity fields do NOT need VIN decoding in this worker.

2. Vehicle registration and DIMO mirrored vehicle onboarding are separate backend domains.
This worker assumes vehicles and DIMO token references already exist.

3. Vehicle reference/service intelligence is a separate domain:
- battery reference specs
- brake reference specs
- tire setups
- tread measurements
- service events

Do NOT mix those into telemetry polling.

------------------------------------------------
PRIMARY OBJECTIVE
------------------------------------------------

Implement a polling-first DIMO telemetry worker system for SynqDrive MVP.

Telemetry behavior:

A) Full latest snapshot polling
- poll every 30 seconds
- only for active connected registered vehicles
- use DIMO latest-signal query style
- fetch a normalized latest state snapshot

B) Live-map polling
- poll every 5 seconds
- only for vehicles currently in an active live tracking session
- fetch only minimal location signals
- keep payloads lightweight

C) Historical analytics fetching
- NEVER continuously poll historical series
- only fetch on demand when analytics tabs/views are opened
- use DIMO historical/range query style
- cache results briefly

------------------------------------------------
OUT OF SCOPE
------------------------------------------------

Do NOT implement here:
- VIN decoding
- battery reference enrichment
- brake reference enrichment
- tire specs enrichment
- product licensing
- Master Admin CRUD
- vehicle registration forms
- prospect logic

------------------------------------------------
DIMO QUERY MODEL
------------------------------------------------

Use a GraphQL-based DIMO telemetry access pattern.

Use latest/current signal queries for:
- latest snapshot polling
- live-map polling

Use historical signal queries for:
- chart data
- trends
- analytics views

Vehicle data access requires a Vehicle JWT.
Vehicle JWT acquisition and refresh must happen server-side only.

------------------------------------------------
LATEST SNAPSHOT SIGNALS
------------------------------------------------

For the 30-second full snapshot poll, fetch and normalize fields such as:

- lastSeen
- currentLocationCoordinates
- powertrainTransmissionTravelledDistance
- powertrainCombustionEngineEngineOilRelativeLevel
- powertrainCombustionEngineDieselExhaustFluidLevel
- powertrainRange
- chassisAxleRow1WheelLeftTirePressure
- chassisAxleRow1WheelRightTirePressure
- chassisAxleRow2WheelLeftTirePressure
- chassisAxleRow2WheelRightTirePressure
- powertrainTractionBatteryStateOfChargeCurrent
- obdEngineLoad
- lowVoltageBatteryCurrentVoltage
- powertrainFuelSystemRelativeLevel
- powertrainFuelSystemAbsoluteLevel

The exact signal set may evolve, but the worker must support a normalized latest-state model.

------------------------------------------------
LIVE MAP SIGNALS
------------------------------------------------

For 5-second live-map polling, fetch only:

- lastSeen
- currentLocationCoordinates

Do not fetch heavy snapshot data in the live-map worker.

------------------------------------------------
ANALYTICS FETCH BEHAVIOR
------------------------------------------------

Historical analytics queries are created on demand by the backend API layer when a user opens analytics views.

Example chart categories:
- speed trends
- travelled distance
- tire pressure history
- location history / map paths
- battery SOC trends
- fuel level trends

The worker should:
- fetch the requested series
- normalize it into chart-ready output
- cache it with deterministic cache keys

------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURE REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------

Use clear separation between:

1. scheduling
2. queueing
3. processing
4. DIMO auth / token management
5. telemetry query execution
6. normalization
7. persistence
8. logging / observability

API controllers must NOT directly call DIMO for heavy polling work.
The API should enqueue work and read SynqDrive-owned persisted data or cached analytics.

------------------------------------------------
REQUIRED QUEUES
------------------------------------------------

Use BullMQ queues for:

- dimo.snapshot.poll
- dimo.live-map.poll
- dimo.analytics.fetch
- dimo.vehicle.sync   (optional but recommended for syncing mirrored DIMO fleet metadata)

------------------------------------------------
REQUIRED SCHEDULERS
------------------------------------------------

1. Snapshot scheduler
- every 30 seconds
- enqueue snapshot jobs for active connected registered vehicles

2. Live-map scheduler
- every 5 seconds
- enqueue jobs only for vehicles with active live tracking sessions

3. Analytics fetch
- no global scheduler
- enqueue only on demand

4. Optional DIMO vehicle mirror sync scheduler
- periodic sync of mirrored DIMO fleet metadata
- this is separate from telemetry polling

------------------------------------------------
PROCESSING BEHAVIOR
------------------------------------------------

Snapshot worker:
- receives vehicleId, dimoTokenId, optional source
- gets valid Vehicle JWT
- executes latest snapshot query
- normalizes payload
- upserts telemetry latest-state table
- writes polling log
- retries transient failures
- uses safe backoff

Live-map worker:
- receives vehicleId, dimoTokenId, optional source
- gets valid Vehicle JWT
- executes location-only query
- writes lightweight position update and/or emits websocket/pubsub event placeholder
- avoids duplicate excessive writes

Analytics worker:
- receives vehicleId, dimoTokenId, from, to, interval, chartType, optional source
- gets valid Vehicle JWT
- executes historical query
- normalizes series
- writes analytics cache
- returns or makes cached result available

Optional DIMO vehicle mirror sync worker:
- syncs DIMO source vehicles into a mirror table
- supports Non Registered Vehicles flow
- does NOT register vehicles automatically into SynqDrive

------------------------------------------------
DIMO AUTH REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------

Implement a dedicated DimoAuthService with:

- getDeveloperJwt()
- getVehicleJwt(tokenId: number)
- getCachedVehicleJwt(tokenId: number)
- refreshVehicleJwt(tokenId: number)

Requirements:
- Redis cache
- expiry-aware refresh
- safety margin before expiry
- per-token lock/deduplication
- server-side only

------------------------------------------------
PERSISTENCE TABLES / MODELS
------------------------------------------------

Propose Prisma models or SQL designs for at least:

1. VehicleLatestState
One row per registered vehicle with the latest normalized telemetry snapshot.

Suggested fields:
- id
- vehicleId
- dimoTokenId
- source
- lastSeenAt
- latitude
- longitude
- odometerKm
- oilLevelRelative
- defLevel
- rangeKm
- tirePressureFl
- tirePressureFr
- tirePressureRl
- tirePressureRr
- evSoc
- engineLoad
- lvBatteryVoltage
- fuelLevelRelative
- fuelLevelAbsolute
- rawPayloadJson
- updatedAt

2. DimoPollLog
Used for diagnostics and operational observability.

Suggested fields:
- id
- vehicleId
- jobType
- status
- startedAt
- finishedAt
- durationMs
- tokenRefreshed
- errorMessage
- errorCode
- retryCount
- metaJson

3. VehiclePositionUpdate
Optional short-lived recent position updates table.
Useful for live map or short retention history.

4. AnalyticsCache
Suggested fields:
- id
- vehicleId
- chartType
- rangeFrom
- rangeTo
- interval
- source
- cacheKey
- payloadJson
- expiresAt
- createdAt

5. Optional DimoVehicleMirror
If mirrored DIMO fleet sync is implemented.

------------------------------------------------
FOLDER STRUCTURE
------------------------------------------------

Use a production-style structure like:

src/
  modules/
    dimo/
      dimo.module.ts
      dimo-auth.service.ts
      dimo-telemetry.service.ts
      dimo-query-builder.ts
      dimo-vehicle-sync.service.ts
      queries/
        latest-vehicle-snapshot.query.ts
        last-seen-location.query.ts
        analytics/
          vehicle-location.query.ts
          performance-timeseries.query.ts
          vehicle-speed.query.ts
          travelled-distance.query.ts
          tire-pressure.query.ts

    jobs/
      jobs.module.ts
      queues/
        dimo-snapshot.queue.ts
        dimo-live-map.queue.ts
        dimo-analytics.queue.ts
        dimo-vehicle-sync.queue.ts
      processors/
        dimo-snapshot.processor.ts
        dimo-live-map.processor.ts
        dimo-analytics.processor.ts
        dimo-vehicle-sync.processor.ts
      schedulers/
        dimo-snapshot.scheduler.ts
        dimo-live-map.scheduler.ts
        dimo-vehicle-sync.scheduler.ts

    telemetry/
      telemetry.module.ts
      telemetry-normalizer.service.ts
      telemetry-persistence.service.ts
      vehicle-latest-state.service.ts
      analytics-cache.service.ts
      polling-log.service.ts

    vehicles/
      vehicles.module.ts
      vehicle.service.ts
      vehicle-tracking-session.service.ts

  shared/
    redis/
      redis.module.ts
      redis.service.ts
    db/
      prisma.service.ts
    logging/
      app-logger.service.ts

------------------------------------------------
IMPLEMENTATION STYLE
------------------------------------------------

- TypeScript only
- NestJS-style modules/services/providers
- BullMQ queues and processors
- Prisma persistence
- env-based configuration
- production-oriented naming
- modular monolith compatible

Final goal:
Design the DIMO telemetry worker architecture for SynqDrive in a way that is correct for the current SynqDrive platform architecture and remains cleanly separated from vehicle onboarding, product licensing, and vehicle reference/service intelligence.